# Braised chicken with taro
> Active time: 30 minutes [Active time] | Total time: 2 hours [Total time]
> #Szechuan style braised #chicken with taro. Taken from Fuschia Dunlop's book. #maindish #asian #chinese

## Prep work

Cut chicken into 3-4cm cubes.

Mix chicken pieces with soy sauce and Shaoxing wine.

- Chicken thighs | 1 lbs | deboned
- dark soy sauce | 1/2 tsp | 
- Shaoxing wine | 1 tbsp | 

Peel taro and cut into 1-2 in cubes.

> raw taro skins can make your hands itch - wear rubber gloves if available

- baby taro | 1 lbs | 

Smack scallions to loosen.

- scallions | 2 | white part only

## Sear chicken

Heat 2 tbsp oil in a wok over high heat

- oil | 2 tbsp | 

Add chicken pieces and spread them evenly across the work. Fry for 1 to 2 minutes [Chicken sear], turning a few times, until pale or with a tinge of gold.

Remove chicken from wok and clean wok.

## Putting it together

Heat 4 tbsp oil in a wok over medium heat.

- oil | 4 tbsp | 

Add chilies bean paste, cardamom, star anise, and cinnamon bark to the wok. Stir-fry until oil is red and fragrant.

- Sichuan chile bean paste | 3.5 tbsp | 
- cinnamon bark | 1 small piece | 
- star anise | 1/2 | 
- cardamom pod | 1 | lightly smashed

Add the garlic, ginger, and scallion whites and stir-fry until fragrant.

- garlic | 1 tbsp | finely chopped
- ginger | 1 tbsp | finely chopped

Add in dried chilies, ground chilies, Sichuan peppercorns and stir-fry until aromatic.

- dried chilies | 6 | halved and deseeded
- ground chilies | 1 tbsp | 
- Sichuan peppercorns | 1 tsp | 

Now add chicken, taro, and little of stock to the wok and stir well.

- chicken stock | 3 cups | 

## Braise it

Transfer to a saucepan or pot and add remaining stock. Add more until the taro and chicken pieces are covered.

Bring to a boil and add salt to taste ( this will get reduced so keep that in mind). Then cover and simmer for about 30 minutes [Braise time].

> remove the aromatics ( star anise, cardamom, cinnamon) if desired

Turn heat up to high and boil for 5 minutes [Reduction time] to reduce the liquid if you want.
